13. LEONIAS (LEONIUS).-“ Leonias de Dundraynon, a monk of Melros'' is the entry in the Monasticon, with the date 1238 prefixed to the name, but without the usual citation of autho- rity. The last note will suffice to show that the statement is one made, partly at least, in error. The Chronica entry touching his accession to the Abbacy is “Anno MccxxxiX, Dominus Rogerus, Abbas RievalliS, suo cessit officio, et Dominus Leonius de Dundraynan, et monachus de Melros, successit?
